	<key>readme</key>
	<string># Confluence Search

Search your Atlassian Cloud Confluence instance from Alfred, scoped to a configurable list of spaces.

## Setup

1. Generate an Atlassian API token at https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
2. Click the `[x]` icon at the top-right of this workflow and fill in:
   - **Confluence base URL** — e.g. `https://yourcompany.atlassian.net`
   - **Atlassian email** — the email on your Atlassian account
   - **API token** — the token you just generated
   - **Space keys** — comma-separated, e.g. `DOCS,ENG,HR`. Leave blank to search all spaces you can see.
3. Open Alfred and type `cf` followed by a search term. Press Return on a result to open it in your browser.
</string>
